gories in this period, On Hysteria focuses not on institutions but on narrative strategies and writing—the ways that texts in a wide range of genres helped to build knowledge through misinterpretation and recontextualized citation. Powerfully interdisciplinary, and offering access to rare historical material for the first time in English, On Hysteria will speak to scholars in a wide range of fields, including the history of science, French studies, and comparative literature.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aHysteria in literature. 0aHysteriavEarly works to 1800. 0aHysteriaxHistory. 0aHysteriaxSocial aspects. 0aHysteriazFrancexHistoryy18th century. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh  ahysteria, psychology, women, gender, healthcare, medicine, aristocracy, class, french revolution, therapy, 18th century, 19th, science, history, comparative literature, france, vaporous affection, religion, diagnosis, proteus, chameleon, hydra, pathology, fits, vapors, gothic, sexual difference, mental illness, health, sexuality, technology, metaphor, narrative, writing, bourgeois culture, modernity, freud, protest, resistance, feminism, enlightenment, neuropsychology, nonfiction, emotion.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311069043940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226275680423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226275680/original  a978-3-11-069043-9  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles